### pgauthzd NATIVE write API examples against the demo model.
###
### Target: the native write path  POST /pgauthz/v1/{write,delete,delete-user,write-checked}.
### Between writes, reads via /pgauthz/v1/check verify the effect.
###
### PORT (published by compose-authzen.yml):
###   * :8092  pgauthzd-full (full profile, writer-capable DB role pgauthzd_rw)
###            — the ONLY instance that can write. @baseUrl below points here.
### The native write path is deliberately absent everywhere else:
###   * :8090  pgauthzd-decision (read-only role) → 403 on any write.
###   * :8091  pgauthzd-opa public listener → 404 (writes go through OPA's
###            internal write callback, not the public AuthZEN surface).
###
### AUTH: every write needs a valid JWT (401 otherwise). Reuse the pre-minted
### demo tokens from http-client.env.json (select the "dev" environment):
### {{access_token_alice}} etc. — ES256-signed with opa/keys/demo.key.txt
### (iss https://auth.example.com, aud authz-api). Mint fresh ones with
### tests/test-authzen.sh's make_token, or from Keycloak (keycloak/get-token.sh).
###
### performed_by (the audit author): an explicit body value wins; otherwise it
### defaults to the authenticated JWT subject. On the OPA write callback OPA
### passes the authenticated subject here explicitly — mirror that by setting it.
### NOTE: the demo/test stack runs with ALLOW_SUBJECT_OVERRIDE=true (env.sh), so
### tuple subjects are taken from the body as written.
###
### Requires: docker compose up (bootstrap.sh) with compose-authzen.yml.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8092
@token = {{access_token_alice}}

### =====================================================================
### WRITE (upsert) TUPLES  (POST /pgauthz/v1/write)
### Body: { "tuples": [ <write_tuples_jsonb elements> ], "performed_by"?,
###         "consistency"? }. Tuple element fields: user_type, user_id,
### relation, object_type, object_id, and optional user_relation,
### condition_name, context, expires_at. Response: { "store", "written": N }
### =====================================================================

### Grant alice viewer on a new document
POST {{baseUrl}}/pgauthz/v1/write
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "tuples": [
    { "user_type": "internal_user", "user_id": "alice", "relation": "viewer", "object_type": "document", "object_id": "doc_test_001" }
  ],
  "performed_by": "http-client"
}
### Expected: { "store": "demo", "written": 1 }

###

### Verify: alice can now read doc_test_001 (viewer → can_read)
POST {{baseUrl}}/pgauthz/v1/check
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject":  { "type": "internal_user", "id": "alice" },
  "action":   { "name": "can_read" },
  "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_test_001" }
}
### Expected: { "allowed": true }

###

### Batch write — grant several users in one call (duplicates are upserts)
POST {{baseUrl}}/pgauthz/v1/write
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "tuples": [
    { "user_type": "internal_user", "user_id": "alice", "relation": "editor", "object_type": "document", "object_id": "doc_test_001" },
    { "user_type": "internal_user", "user_id": "bob",   "relation": "viewer", "object_type": "document", "object_id": "doc_test_001" }
  ],
  "performed_by": "http-client"
}
### Expected: { "store": "demo", "written": 2 }

###

### Write a tuple with an expiry (temporary grant) + explicit condition/context.
### expires_at, condition_name, and context are optional per-tuple fields.
POST {{baseUrl}}/pgauthz/v1/write
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "tuples": [
    {
      "user_type": "internal_user",
      "user_id": "alice",
      "relation": "viewer",
      "object_type": "document",
      "object_id": "doc_test_temp",
      "expires_at": "2030-01-01T00:00:00Z"
    }
  ],
  "performed_by": "http-client"
}
### Expected: { "store": "demo", "written": 1 }

###

### Store-scoped write variant — /stores/{store}/pgauthz/v1/write
POST {{baseUrl}}/stores/demo/pgauthz/v1/write
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "tuples": [
    { "user_type": "internal_user", "user_id": "bob", "relation": "editor", "object_type": "document", "object_id": "doc_test_001" }
  ],
  "performed_by": "http-client"
}
### Expected: { "store": "demo", "written": 1 }

###

### =====================================================================
### DELETE TUPLES  (POST /pgauthz/v1/delete)
### Same body shape as /write. Response: { "store", "deleted": N }
### =====================================================================

### Revoke a single tuple — alice's viewer on doc_test_001
POST {{baseUrl}}/pgauthz/v1/delete
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "tuples": [
    { "user_type": "internal_user", "user_id": "alice", "relation": "viewer", "object_type": "document", "object_id": "doc_test_001" }
  ],
  "performed_by": "http-client"
}
### Expected: { "store": "demo", "deleted": 1 }

###

### Batch delete — remove multiple tuples in one call
POST {{baseUrl}}/pgauthz/v1/delete
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "tuples": [
    { "user_type": "internal_user", "user_id": "alice", "relation": "editor", "object_type": "document", "object_id": "doc_test_001" },
    { "user_type": "internal_user", "user_id": "bob",   "relation": "viewer", "object_type": "document", "object_id": "doc_test_001" },
    { "user_type": "internal_user", "user_id": "bob",   "relation": "editor", "object_type": "document", "object_id": "doc_test_001" }
  ],
  "performed_by": "http-client"
}
### Expected: { "store": "demo", "deleted": 3 }

###

### Verify: bob can no longer read doc_test_001
POST {{baseUrl}}/pgauthz/v1/check
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject":  { "type": "internal_user", "id": "bob" },
  "action":   { "name": "can_read" },
  "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_test_001" }
}
### Expected: { "allowed": false }

###

### =====================================================================
### DELETE ALL TUPLES FOR A USER — offboarding  (POST /pgauthz/v1/delete-user)
### Body: { "user": { "type": <user_type>, "id": <user_id> }, "performed_by"?,
###         "consistency"? }. Response: { "store", "deleted": N }
### =====================================================================

### Seed a throwaway grant, then wipe everything for the user.
POST {{baseUrl}}/pgauthz/v1/write
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "tuples": [
    { "user_type": "internal_user", "user_id": "__offboard_test__", "relation": "viewer", "object_type": "document", "object_id": "doc_test_001" }
  ],
  "performed_by": "http-client"
}
### Expected: { "store": "demo", "written": 1 }

###

### Revoke ALL access for the offboarded user
POST {{baseUrl}}/pgauthz/v1/delete-user
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user": { "type": "internal_user", "id": "__offboard_test__" },
  "performed_by": "offboarding"
}
### Expected: { "store": "demo", "deleted": 1 }

###

### =====================================================================
### CONDITIONAL / ATOMIC WRITE  (POST /pgauthz/v1/write-checked)
### Preconditions gate the deletes+writes; all-or-nothing (optimistic
### concurrency). Body: { "preconditions"?, "deletes"?, "writes"?,
###   "performed_by"?, "consistency"? } — each is a JSONB array. The engine's
### JSONB result is returned verbatim (committed/applied counts, etc.).
### =====================================================================

### Grant editor to carol ONLY IF a viewer tuple already exists (precondition).
POST {{baseUrl}}/pgauthz/v1/write-checked
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "preconditions": [
    { "match": "exists", "user_type": "internal_user", "user_id": "alice", "relation": "viewer", "object_type": "document", "object_id": "doc_test_002" }
  ],
  "writes": [
    { "user_type": "internal_user", "user_id": "carol", "relation": "editor", "object_type": "document", "object_id": "doc_test_002" }
  ],
  "performed_by": "http-client"
}
### Expected: engine JSONB result. If the precondition fails, no write is applied.

###

### Atomic swap — delete the old grant and add a new one in one transaction.
POST {{baseUrl}}/pgauthz/v1/write-checked
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "deletes": [
    { "user_type": "internal_user", "user_id": "carol", "relation": "editor", "object_type": "document", "object_id": "doc_test_002" }
  ],
  "writes": [
    { "user_type": "internal_user", "user_id": "carol", "relation": "viewer", "object_type": "document", "object_id": "doc_test_002" }
  ],
  "performed_by": "http-client"
}
### Expected: engine JSONB result (deletes + writes applied atomically)

###

### Cleanup: remove the write-checked test tuples
POST {{baseUrl}}/pgauthz/v1/delete
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "tuples": [
    { "user_type": "internal_user", "user_id": "carol", "relation": "viewer", "object_type": "document", "object_id": "doc_test_002" },
    { "user_type": "internal_user", "user_id": "alice", "relation": "viewer", "object_type": "document", "object_id": "doc_test_temp" }
  ],
  "performed_by": "cleanup"
}
### Expected: { "store": "demo", "deleted": <n> }

###

### =====================================================================
### SECURITY — writes must be authenticated and writer-capable
### =====================================================================

### No token → 401 (unauthenticated)
POST {{baseUrl}}/pgauthz/v1/write
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "tuples": [
    { "user_type": "internal_user", "user_id": "eve", "relation": "viewer", "object_type": "document", "object_id": "doc_payroll_001" }
  ]
}
### Expected: HTTP 401

###

### Same write against the read-only decision-only instance (:8090) → 403.
### The security boundary is the DB role: pgauthzd-decision physically cannot write.
POST http://localhost:8090/pgauthz/v1/write
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "tuples": [
    { "user_type": "internal_user", "user_id": "alice", "relation": "viewer", "object_type": "document", "object_id": "doc_test_001" }
  ],
  "performed_by": "http-client"
}
### Expected: HTTP 403 (this instance is read-only / decision-only profile)
